DCI detectives have arrested two I&M bank staff for allegedly stealing over Sh27 million. Tom Odhiambo Adinda and Daniel Ochieng both employees of the bank's Kisii Branch were arrested on Friday. "Both employees of I&M Bank - Kisii Branch and Key Vault custodians were arrested yesterday for stealing over Sh.27Million from the bank by mixing 100 and 1000 notes in each 1M bundle of notes," DCI said in a tweet on Saturday. They are expected to appear in court on Monday. Click here for the latest political news